## 1. Task Intent Interpretation
### 1.1 Problem Summary
NuttyFans needs foundational authentication and identity safeguards: email/password registration, social login (Google, Apple), email verification, password reset, and an age-verification gate using a third-party provider. These flows are prerequisites for user onboarding, compliance (adult-content gating), and downstream features.

### 1.2 Goals
- Enable friction-balanced onboarding while enforcing trust/safety (18+).
- Support federated sign-in to reduce drop-off (Google, Apple).
- Ensure account integrity via email verification and password reset.
- Integrate age verification using an external provider suitable for global, mixed-content use.

### 1.3 Success Criteria (high level)
- Users can create accounts and sign in via email/password or Google/Apple.
- Email verification required before full access; unverified users have limited access.
- Password reset completes end-to-end with secure tokens.
- Age gate blocks under-18 access using third-party verification; provides clear allow/deny/appeal states.
- Sessions and sign-out behave predictably across web and future mobile.

