## 3. Research (Patterns & Considerations)
### 3.1 Authentication & Identity Patterns
- **Progressive friction:** allow starting with social login but require age + email verification before accessing restricted content.
- **Stateful onboarding:** maintain intermediate states (email-unverified, age-pending, age-denied) and gate features accordingly.
- **Session hygiene:** short-lived sessions with refresh where applicable; explicit sign-out clears sessions on all devices (design detail to be defined in engineering).
- **Recovery-first UX:** password reset emails must be time-bound, single-use, and rate-limited.

### 3.2 Social Login (Google, Apple)
- Google: standard OAuth 2.0 with email scope; handle missing verified email edge cases.
- Apple: supports private relay emails; must surface “sign in with Apple” compliance copy and handle non-recoverable relay addresses (users deleting relay).
- Account linking: avoid duplicate accounts by matching provider email when verified; if mismatch, require explicit linking flow (backend policy to define).

### 3.3 Email Verification
- Required before accessing age-restricted content or payments.
- Link must be single-use, time-bound; clear expired link messaging with resend.
- Track verification status at user level; support re-send with rate limits.

### 3.4 Password Reset
- Tokenized reset links (single-use, time-bound).
- Post-reset forced re-auth across sessions.
- Rate limit requests; do not reveal account existence (generic messaging).

### 3.5 Age Verification (Third-Party) — Options for NuttyFans
We need global coverage, adult-content friendliness, strong fraud controls, and fast UX. Top candidates:

| Vendor | Why It Fits | Considerations |
|--------|-------------|----------------|
| **Persona** | Strong SDKs, global docs support, age estimation + document verification, flexible policies | Pricing at scale; DPIA/DP handling needed |
| **Veriff** | High accuracy, supports video/selfie + docs, good fraud prevention | Can be stricter UX; pricing premium |
| **Onfido** | Mature KYC/age checks, liveness, broad ID coverage | May require custom flows for age-only use |
| **Jumio** | Fast verification, liveness, document breadth | Cost; integration complexity |
| **Yoti** | Privacy-forward, age estimation & reusable digital ID, good for age-gate | Coverage varies by country; brand recognition lower in US |

Recommendation criteria (to decide in architecture/legal):
- Content tolerance (adult use accepted).
- Global coverage (IDs + biometrics).
- Fraud/liveness strength.
- SDK/web UX quality and time-to-verify.
- Data residency, GDPR/CCPA compliance, retention controls.
- Pricing at projected volume (Year 1: 500k users).

### 3.6 Compliance & Trust/Safety Notes
- BRD/PRD call out strict 18+ gating (PRD U-003).
- Must avoid revealing whether an email exists (privacy).
- Need auditability of verification outcomes (who/when/provider result).
- Accessibility: all flows keyboard/reader friendly.

