## 5. Non-Functional Requirements
- NFR-SEC-001: Enforce strong password policy; hash storage (implementation detail to backend).
- NFR-SEC-002: Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints (login, register, verification resend, reset request).
- NFR-SEC-003: Secrets managed via environment variables; no secrets in repo.
- NFR-PRIV-001: Do not disclose account existence in responses.
- NFR-COMPL-001: Age verification data handling aligns with GDPR/CCPA; retention and deletion policies documented.
- NFR-UX-001: Flows are accessible (WCAG 2.1 AA for forms, focus states).
- NFR-REL-001: Email delivery reliability tracked (bounce handling), but provider selection is out of scope.

