## 7. Open Questions (needs human/architecture/legal input)
| ID | Question | Decision/Notes |
|----|----------|----------------|
| Q1 | Which age verification vendor? | **Veriff** — global coverage, adult-content tolerant, strong fraud/liveness; fallback vendor can be reassessed if coverage gaps emerge. |
| Q2 | Password policy (length/complexity/breach check)? | **Min 12 chars**, require upper+lower+digit+symbol; block common/breached passwords via k-anon HIBP; prevent recent password reuse; lockout/rate-limit login attempts. |
| Q3 | Session duration and refresh strategy? | **Idle 12h**, absolute 30d cap with “keep me signed in”; rotate/refresh at sign-in and every 12h; force re-auth after password reset or state changes (lock/age-denied). |
| Q4 | Account linking rules (social + email)? | One canonical account per verified email. Auto-link if provider email is verified and matches existing verified email. If mismatch: require sign-in with canonical account then link; block creating a new account with a different verified email from the same identity. Handle Apple relay by encouraging primary email addition post-signup. |
| Q5 | What age-provider data to store and retention period? | Store minimal: provider session/reference ID, result (pass/fail/pending), method type, verification timestamps, DOB confirmation flag, country, and liveness/fraud score (if provided). **Purge raw documents/biometrics within 30 days**; keep long-term audit record of status + timestamps only. |
| Q6 | Geo restrictions that affect gating? | **Global launch**; no geo blocks now. Keep a configurable allow/deny list for future policy changes; rely on provider coverage and surface graceful fallback if unsupported country. |

